   "source": [
    "# Project proposal\n",
    "**Research Question**\n",
    "\n",
    "Do a book's rating and its ranking predict how many votes it receives?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Motivation**\n",
    "\n",
    "I would like to see if the ranking or rating are related to the amount of votes the books has. \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "**Data**\n",
    "\n",
    "Variables to collect by web scraping\n",
    "\n",
    "- Titles\n",
    "- Authors\n",
    "- Ratings\n",
    "- Votes\n",
    "- Rankings\n",
    "  \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 218,
   "id": "4a078791-ee61-49c2-8a8c-edb6021aa879",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<title>Top 100 Books of All Time – Books Guru</title>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 218,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# import requests\n",
    "# import pandas as pd\n",
    "url = \"https://books-guru.com/top-100-books\"\n",
    "response = requests.get(url)\n",
    "soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text)\n",
    "soup.title"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ec18eab-495c-4f49-866f-848399648114",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Regression Model**\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\text{Votes}_i = \\beta_0 + \\beta_1 \\cdot \\text{Rating}_i + \\beta_2 \\cdot \\text{Ranking}_i + \\epsilon_i\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where:\n",
    "- $\\text{Votes}_i$ represents the number of votes for book $i$\n",
    "- $\\text{Rating}_i$ represents the rating for book $i$ (0-5)\n",
    "- $\\text{Ranking}_i$ represents the list position of book $i$ (1 -100)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "They are going to be normalized by using z_score for the regression"
   ]
  },
  {
